Lagos – Four Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) clubs are in hot pursuit of Wikki Tourists attacking midfielder Abubakar “Korea” Aliyu Ibrahim. The former Flying Eagles of Nigeria star has been in blistering form for the ‘Yankari Elephants’ since joining from former Nigerian Champions Akwa United in 2021. DAILY INDEPENDENT gathered that current Champions Rivers United are top on the list of the clubs who have shown interest for his services, with Akwa United set to renew their interest Others are 2017 Champions Rangers International of Enugu and Gombe United of Gombe. Abubakar Ibrahim scored eight goals for the ‘Yankari Elephants’, but no official bid for his services from the mentioned clubs. Wikki Tourists will have to make sure to keep him to the club plan for next season campaign as the reports coming in from Bauchi, which has it, that Wikki Tourists main target is to return to Continental engagement next season. Wikki Tourists make the list of top 10 clubs in the just concluded Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) after their 2-0 demolition of relegated Katsina United at their fortress Abubakar Tafawa Balewa Stadium on Sunday.